ADDITIONAL TERMS (Section 13 clarification for MedOverflow):

The MedOverflow software — comprising the qa-core Rust library, identity-verification
adapter crate, ingestion/ETL tooling, and web client — is licensed under AGPL-3.0.

If you modify and run MedOverflow as a network service (including but not limited to:
hosting a Q&A instance, offering MedOverflow-based APIs, or deploying a derivative
as a web application), you must:

1. Disclose the modified source code to all users of your network service
2. Make the source code available under the same AGPL-3.0 license
3. Retain this notice and all copyright attributions

This is the network-copyleft provision (AGPL §13). It ensures that improvements
to MedOverflow made by a network operator are shared back to the community.

